'''Aleksandr Sergeyevich Ivanchenkov''' ({{lang-ru|Алекса́ндр Серге́евич Иванче́нков}}; born 28 September 1940 ) is a retired [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[astronaut|cosmonaut]] who flew as Flight Engineer on [[Soyuz 29]] and [[Soyuz T-6]], he spent 147 days, 12 hours and 37 minutes in space.

== Biography ==
Ivanchenkov is married with one child.  He was selected as a cosmonaut on 27 March 1973. He retired on 3 November 1993.

==Honours and awards==
*Twice [[Hero of the Soviet Union]];
*[[Pilot-Cosmonaut of the USSR]];
*Two [[Order of Lenin|Orders of Lenin]];
*[[Medal "For Merit in Space Exploration"]] (Russian Federation);
*Hero of the German Democratic Republic;
*[[Order of Karl Marx]];
*Commander of the [[Legion of Honour]] (France);
*[[Cross of Grunwald]] 3rd class.

