{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Boydell Glacier | other_name = | photo = Ant-pen-map-Trinity-Peninsula.PNG | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land, Antarctica | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Boydell in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = | location = [[Trinity Peninsula]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|11|S|59|4|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|9|nmi|0|abbr=on}} | width = | thickness = unknown | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Sjögren Inlet]] | status = unknown | embedded = }}
'''Boydell Glacier''' ({{Coord|64|11|S|59|4|W|source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a [[glacier]] on [[Trinity Peninsula]] in northern [[Graham Land]]. It is about {{convert|9|mi}} long, flowing southeastward from [[Detroit Plateau]] to enter [[Sjögren Inlet]] in [[Prince Gustav Channel]] north of the [[glacier terminus|terminus]] of [[Sjögren Glacier]] and {{convert|6|mi|0}} west of [[Mount Wild (Graham Land)|Mount Wild]]. It was mapped by the [[Falkland Islands Dependencies Survey]] from surveys (1960–61), and named by the [[UK Antarctic Place-Names Committee]] for [[James Boydell]], English inventor of a [[steam traction engine]], the first practical [[Continuous track|track-laying vehicle]].
