{{unsourced|date=April 2017}}
In radiological physics, '''charged-particle equilibrium''' (CPE) occurs when the number of [[charged particle]]s leaving a volume is equal to the number entering, for each energy and type of particle.  When CPE exists in an irradiated medium, the [[absorbed dose]] in the volume is equal to the collision [[Kerma (physics)|kerma]]. 

In order for this to occur, energy is needed. 

